# Walkthrough - Session Reminders & Abandoned Cart Recovery

I have implemented the student lifecycle automation as requested, following the backend patterns of the project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Data Model & Lifecycle Hooks
- Added tracking fields to [Bookings.ts](file:///d:/projects/nextacademy/src/collections/Bookings.ts):
    - `reminderSent24h`, `reminderSent1h`
    - `cartRecovery1hSent`, `cartRecovery24hSent`
    - `checkoutStartedAt`
- Implemented a `beforeChange` hook to automatically set `checkoutStartedAt` when a new `pending` booking is created. This enables the abandoned cart cron to accurately calculate elapsed time.

### 2. Email Automation
- Created [reminder-emails.ts](file:///d:/projects/nextacademy/src/lib/email/reminder-emails.ts) with `sendSessionReminder`:
    - Supports 24-hour and 1-hour reminders.
    - Includes bilingual templates (AR/EN).
- Created [abandoned-cart-emails.ts](file:///d:/projects/nextacademy/src/lib/email/abandoned-cart-emails.ts) with `sendAbandonedCartEmail`:
    - Handles 1-hour "nudge" and 24-hour "urgency" follow-ups.
    - Includes bilingual templates.
- Updated the main email index to export these new utilities.

### 3. Cron Endpoints
- Implemented `/api/cron/session-reminders`:
    - Scans for upcoming sessions in 24h and 1h windows.
    - Notifies confirmed students who haven't received a reminder yet.
- Implemented `/api/cron/abandoned-cart`:
    - Identifies pending checkouts initiated 1h and 24h ago.
    - Triggers recovery emails to reduce drop-off.
- Updated [vercel.json](file:///d:/projects/nextacademy/vercel.json) to register these schedules.

